courses.description: Fall, Spring, Summer. Description of the various objects found in the heavens as well as the principles and techniques employed in investigations of these objects.
Fall, Spring, Summer. Prerequisite: AA 100 or concurrent registration. Observations of the various objects found in the heavens with 5-inch reflecting telescope.
Summer. Must register for lecture and laboratory. Astronomical objects in the night and day sky; observation with 16-inch telescope.

Fall (odd years). Prerequisite: MATH 124; MATH 126; PH 110 or PH 121 or PH 141. Must register for lecture and laboratory. Celestial mechanics, earth-moon systems, planets and satellites, interplanetary medium, origin of solar system.

Spring (odd years). Prerequisite: MATH 124 and MATH 126; PH 110 or PH 121 or PH 141. Must register for lecture and laboratory. Properties of sun and stars, variable stars, binary and multiple star systems, star clusters, interstellar medium, stellar evolution.

Fall (even years). Prerequisite: MATH 124; MATH 126; PH 110 or PH 121 or PH 141. Must register for lecture and laboratory. Properties of the Milky Way, galaxies, quasars and related objects; special and general relativity; cosmology.
Fall, Spring, Summer Prerequisite: Written consent of instructor.
Fall, Spring, Summer. Credit not allowed for both ACT 205 and ACT 210. For nonbusiness majors. Understanding of financial statements to support financial and managerial decision making.
Fall, Spring, Summer. Prerequisite: ACT 205 or ACT 210; BUS 150 or concurrent registration or CS 110 or concurrent registration. Use of accounting information in internal decision making.
